\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 In the United Arab Emirates, it is strictly forbidden to swear. Using obscene language is considered a crime. You may be imprisoned for up to a year for violation or fined nearly 10,000. If you show someone on the middle finger, you are immediately deported.\
The rule on obscene language and gestures also applies to messages on WhatsApp or any other social network or instant messenger. You can receive a fine of up to $ 250,000, imprisonment or deportation.\
it is illegal to \'93invade the privacy of another person\'94 using any gadget and social network. The penalty for this is a minimum 6 months imprisonment and a fine of 100,000 to 500,000 AED.\
