\f1 \cf3 \cb4 \strokec3 The UAE is very strict about preserving the privacy of individuals, and taking a picture of someone without their knowledge or consent is taken very seriously. According to the cybercrime laws, you can be fined up to 500,000 dirhams and jailed for six months for the offence, although in practice the sentences are much harsher, with various visitors having been deported.
